{"id":"int-945fd0871ebbf863a047db00012f6fc1","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-07-02T23:40:48.072714Z","actor":"magenta-rust-impl","issue_id":"magenta-player-iii.6","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"in_progress","reason":"Tested on Apple M5 base tier (32GB). Result: mrt2_small is rock-stable at 8192 (dropped_frames pins at 1, never grows -- strictly better than 4096s baseline). mrt2_base does NOT improve at 8192 -- dropped_frames still grows linearly and unboundedly (76-87/tick at 8192 vs 55-70/tick at 4096), confirming genuine hardware throughput limit (57-74ms/frame vs 40ms budget), not scheduling jitter, exactly matching the docs own predicted caveat. Kept 8192 as new default: strictly better for mrt2_small, neutral for mrt2_base. Documented measured result in docs/realtime-audio.md including the surprising finding that base-tier M5 (newer generation, no Pro/Max memory bandwidth) still cannot run mrt2_base in real time."}}
{"id":"int-43fe2218063f16af418f41464c9f455f","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-07-02T23:44:32.648172Z","actor":"magenta-rust-impl","issue_id":"magenta-player-3vy.3","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"in_progress","old_value":"open"}}
{"id":"int-95b025935fe77434390ee94cf217700f","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-07-03T00:43:35.703414Z","actor":"magenta-rust-impl","issue_id":"magenta-player-3vy.3","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"in_progress","reason":"Implemented --record/--record-seconds/--output-dir flags on the play subcommand, plus persistent output_dir config key (default ~/Documents/Magenta/magenta-rt-v2/recordings, auto-created if missing). Timestamped default filename (recording-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.wav) avoids collisions. Uses engine internal recording buffer (start_recording/stop_recording/get_recorded_sample_count/get_recorded_audio via new const FFI wrappers in bridge.h) -- captures at native 48kHz regardless of live CPAL output fallback rate. Writes 16-bit PCM WAV via hound. --record runs a fixed-duration capture then exits (one-shot utility, not background recording). Verified via ffprobe: valid PCM s16le/48kHz/stereo, probe_score 99. Also fixed a latent bug while adding output_dir: AppConfig lacked #[serde(default)], so any new field addition would fail to parse existing config.toml files and silently reset user settings to factory defaults on next load -- added struct-level #[serde(default)] plus self-healing re-save in load_config() so config list always reflects the full effective config. Documented in rust-player/README.md."}}
