{"id":"int-c900d704653fb4cb5ccdf6d6e5b7801f","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-07-03T00:48:52.841518Z","actor":"magenta-prime-implementor","issue_id":"magenta-player-cxx","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"open","reason":"AppIcon.icns compiled from about-logo.png via sips+iconutil; CFBundleIconFile declared in Info.plist; Makefile copies .icns into bundle on every build"}}
{"id":"int-16a00b392896dc7af6eb0c1ca8c1af48","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-07-03T00:49:05.274712Z","actor":"magenta-rust-impl","issue_id":"magenta-player-iii.7","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"in_progress","reason":"Added reset_dropped_frames() FFI wrapper and call it right after toggle_play(true) (covers both the play and --record code paths). Verified: dropped_frames now shows a flat, non-growing count (8, matching the expected 1-3 frame ring-buffer refill after trigger_reset()) instead of accumulating from model load / CPAL device setup. Metrics now accurately reflect only this sessions real underruns."}}
{"id":"int-d720cd40a6ca890229d51d7790ad1ed9","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-07-03T00:49:09.150358Z","actor":"magenta-rust-impl","issue_id":"magenta-player-iii.8","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"in_progress","old_value":"open"}}
{"id":"int-16b3ef5a3d697e7b1e7f76b1a509195f","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-07-03T00:50:33.77628Z","actor":"magenta-rust-impl","issue_id":"magenta-player-iii.8","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"in_progress","reason":"Added find_resources_near_model() helper that walks up from the model files parent directory looking for a resources/ sibling, per mrt2-integration.md guidance (do not hardcode a level count). Only triggers as a fallback when the configured/default resources path does not exist on disk -- an explicitly-set existing path always wins, so this is purely additive/safe. Verified: pointing --resources at a nonexistent path while providing a valid --model correctly auto-derives and uses the real resources dir, printing an [INFO] message; the normal happy path (default already correct) is unaffected and silent."}}
{"id":"int-cccb07a968f74a0e4393bfcaa0b62945","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-07-03T00:50:41.380274Z","actor":"magenta-rust-impl","issue_id":"magenta-player-iii.9","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"in_progress","old_value":"open"}}
{"id":"int-c9c1bdb88665168d787575545b53dc95","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-07-03T00:52:04.877893Z","actor":"magenta-rust-impl","issue_id":"magenta-player-iii.9","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"in_progress","reason":"Decided: keep factory default (5.0), no change needed -- and no listening test required, the answer is provable from code. Traced populate_condition_tokens() and the neg_notes_ptr construction in mlx_engine.cpp: with no MIDI input wired up in the Rust CLI (note_tracker_ always reports NOTE_IDLE for all 128 pitches), the positive cond_ptr notes section and the negative neg_notes_ptr notes section are byte-identical every frame. Since CFG computes null_output + cfg_weight*(conditioned-null), and conditioned==null for the notes signal here, the contrast term is exactly zero regardless of cfg_notes value -- mathematically a no-op in this CLI until MIDI input exists. Documented this in rust-player/README.md so users are not confused why tweaking cfg_notes has no audible effect. Kept the flag/config key for API completeness and future MIDI support."}}
