{"id":"int-f9948905d8797c99728dfe5453e8fd6e","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-07-03T00:54:06.086242Z","actor":"magenta-prime-implementor","issue_id":"magenta-player-bks","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"in_progress","reason":"TimelineView+Canvas 30fps rolling waveform, WaveformBuffer ring buffer in render block, filled stereo polylines L=blue R=green, fades when not generating"}}
{"id":"int-7b65f937b2eeff5ac41411c17e7a09cb","kind":"field_change","created_at":"2026-07-03T00:56:36.108822Z","actor":"magenta-rust-impl","issue_id":"magenta-player-iii.4","extra":{"field":"status","new_value":"closed","old_value":"in_progress","reason":"Replaced manual print!(\".\") polling loops with indicatif spinners for all three blocking/async phases: MusicCoCa asset init, model load (5-15s compile), and prompt encoding poll. Used enable_steady_tick so the spinner animates via its own background thread even while load_model blocks the main thread synchronously. Caught and fixed a real regression during testing: indicatif silently suppresses ALL drawing (including finish_with_message) when stderr is not a TTY -- would have made piped/logged/CI output lose all three status confirmations. Fixed by using finish_and_clear() plus explicit plain println!/eprintln! for all status text, so the spinner is purely a cosmetic interactive-terminal addition and all informational output is guaranteed to appear in every context (verified via this non-tty test harness). Documented in README."}}
